The paper deals with multi-agent systems and group decision making, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of majority voting and the analysis of computational complexity suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
